  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Core, deseed, and finely dice @Bell Pepper{1}(deseeded and finely diced). Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}(halved, peeled, and finely diced). Place @Garlic{2%cloves} cloves in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @Olive Oil{} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cinch into a packet.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), salt, and pepper. Place garlic foil packet on same sheet. Roast on top rack until potatoes are browned and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}. After ~{15%minutes}, remove garlic from sheet.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and @Sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4). Cook until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

In a large bowl, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, remaining Fry Seasoning, salt (we used ¾ tsp; 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper. Form into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add patties; cook until browned on first side, ~{3-5%minutes}. Flip, top with a small amount of pepper relish, then sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{½%cup}. Continue cooking until cheese melts and patties reach desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} more. TIP: Cover pan to help melt cheese.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @Potato Buns{2}. Once garlic is done, carefully remove from foil and transfer to a #cutting board{}. Mash with a #fork{} until smooth. In a second small bowl, combine mashed garlic and @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread top buns with garlic aioli. Fill buns with patties and as much remaining pepper relish you like. Serve with potato wedges and any remaining pepper relish on the side.